  @{u}PacMan'96 Usage:@{uu}

   After you have started PacMan'96 a Main Menu will apear:

   You can use the joystick or the cursor keys to move the
   arrows up and down, which mark the actual position 
   in the menu.
   If you press the joystick button or the return key
   you move to the selected sub menu.
   By pressing the ESC key you can go back to the
   previous step and move to the main menu.

   Entries in the Main Menu:

                  -> @{" 1P START " Link MainStart} <-

                     @{" OPTIONS  " Link MainOptions}

                     @{" HISCORE  " Link MainHiScore}

                     @{"  EDITOR  " Link MainEditor}

                     @{"   EXIT   " Link MainExit}


   If you press ESC in the main menu you will move to
   the @{" EXIT " Link MainExit} menu.
@Endnode



@Node MainStart "PacMan'96 Documentation - 1P/2P START"
@Toc MainMenu
@Prev MainExit
@Next MainOptions

  @{u}PacMan'96 1P/2P START:@{uu}

   By pressing the left/right cursor keys or by draging
   the joystick left/right you can select <1P START> or
   <2P START> (one or two player start).

   By selecting this menu entry (press enter or the 
   fire button) the game will be started. The rules
   of the game should be well-known - so I don't 
   explain them here again (laziness:)

   * On top oft the screen you find the current scores
     for player 1 (left) and player 2 (right). Between
     them you see the current high score.
   * Beside the screen you see some fruits which
     might be collected in this level.
   * The hearts on the bottom tell you how many lives
     you have left.

   Images for player one are always displayed on the
   left side, for player two the right part of the 
   screen is used.

   While the game is playing you can press ESC or the
   P key or the fire button or the Pause key on the 
   joypad to pause the game.

   A pause menu apears:

                  -> @{"   PAUSE MENU   " Link PauseMenu} <-

                     @{"     POPMAN     " Link PauseMusic}

                     @{" MUSICVOLUME 64 " Link PauseMXVol}

                     @{" SOUNDVOLUME 64 " Link PauseFXVol}

                     @{"    END GAME    " Link EndGame}
@EndNode



