@Node OptTaskPri "PacMan'96 Documentation - TASKPRI"
@Toc MainOptions
@Prev OptFXVol
@Next OptScreen

  @{u}PacMan'96 TASKPRI:@{uu}

   By selecting this entry you change the taskpriority
   of the program.

   Press the left/right cursor key or the joystick
   left/right to decrease or increase the priority
   in a range between 0 and 5.

   <0> standard priority of all programs.

   <1> default, should be ok.

   <2> to <5> to play around (especially for @{" Daniel " Link MrBench}).

   Note: The higher the priority of PacMan'96 the less 
         cpu power is available for the other programs.
@EndNode

